OL,3,CBakery and brewery dramatically cuts
OL,4,Cex-prisoner reoffending
OL,6,F"But as soon as they get asked have
OL,7,Fyou been to prison, it all gets
OL,8,Fknocked back. So if you don't have
OL,9,Fplaces like this then you're going to
OL,10,Fkeep repeating the cycle."
OL,12,FTess Taylor says more needs to be done
OL,13,Fto help ex-offenders into work.
OL,15,F"At the moment we spend about 19-
OL,16,Fbillion a year on reoffending and it
OL,17,Fjust doesn't make sense."
OL,19,F"We spend so much money on locking
OL,20,Fpeople up and then we spend so little
OL,21,Fon resettlement and support."
